Shops.Name: Wolfstack Exchange
Shops.Description: Trading in common goods will only earn slim profits. Seek other opportunities.

Shops.Name: The Iron & Misery Company
Shops.Description: [More powerful engines consume more fuel, but increase speed - essential for large slow ships.]

Shops.Name: Carrow's Naval Surplus
Shops.Description: Mr Carrow has found a use for the equipment once sold to the sadly reduced Royal Navy.

Shops.Name: Caminus Yards
Shops.Description: The dangerously jovial Mr Fires manufactures the most intimidating, least carefully tested devices.

Shops.Name: Mrs Plenty's Shipside Provisioners
Shops.Description: A profitable sideline for the notorious carnival entrepreneuse.

Shops.Name: Bultitude's House of Vision
Shops.Description: Bultitude's political convictions may be suspect, but his ship's lights are reliably excellent.

Shops.Name: Temple of Labours
Shops.Description: BRING MATERIAL.

Name: Port Carnelian Market
Description: Not just sapphires. Although there are quite a lot of sapphires.

Shops.Name: Dockside Market
Shops.Description: The stalls are almost the same as Wolfstack. So are the sounds. The scents are utterly different.

Shops.Name: Sapphire Exchange
Shops.Description: Actually, this place is indeed mostly sapphires.

Name: Adam's Way
Description: The gateway to the Continent's treasures.

Shops.Name: Peleghast's Post
Shops.Description: The sign at the door reads: LICENSED FOR MORTAL TRADE

Name: Market of Hungers
Description: Use a MARKET OF HUNGERS choice under STORY to access more goods.

Shops.Name: Fire in the Belly
Shops.Description: The Market always sells Fuel. Use a MARKET story choice for more goods.

Shops.Name: Arcade of Sighs
Shops.Description: Here the solemn bandaged merchants of the colonies trade old cold coins for brighter things.

Shops.Name: Hollow Temple
Shops.Description: The image of a long-snouted reptile god still stands in the temple, but now storytellers gather here.

Shops.Name: The Charnel Lounge
Shops.Description: Do you have tomb-colonists? Drop them off here for payment.

Shops.Name: Harbour Provisioners
Shops.Description: A sluggish and hostile merchant squints warily. A few goods of indifferent quality are available.

Shops.Name: Licensed Exchange
Shops.Description: High prices for feathers blue as the lost sky; and a few other plums.

Shops.Name: Red Stallion Publishing
Shops.Description: Scrolls, pamphlets, and books in a dozen languages.

Shops.Name: Shipyard
Shops.Description: Equipment

Shops.Name: Fortune & Fortune
Shops.Description: Purveyors of white coke and mutersalt. Payment in stories.

Shops.Name: The Hunter's Cage
Shops.Description: A sign reads: BONES PLEASE. The proprietor will sell you beast-meat for stories, or buy your ivory.

Shops.Name: Malebolge Excavations
Shops.Description: Diggery, lootery and scholary! Also, zzoup.

Shops.Name: Daily Bread
Shops.Description: Palmerston's pernicious pollution poisons provisions.

Shops.Name: The Arrant Limpet
Shops.Description: Always eager for wine and honey. Their supply prices are calibrated for corsairs.

Shops.Name: The Friendly Face
Shops.Description: Of course you can sell illicit goods here. And of course you can't expect to get a fair price.

Name: The Calvary Doctrine
Description: Sacrifice what is needful, and gain that which is desirable.

Shops.Name: The House of Milks
Shops.Description: Coffee and fuel drip from dragon-teats.

Name: The Gesundheit Conspiracy
Description: You will be happy, and healthy. Nothing else remains.

Shops.Name: House of Harvests
Shops.Description: "Take," the merchants tell you. "Eat. Only let us drink."

Shops.Name: House of Pleasures
Shops.Description: The flies will caress you with their wings. Hurry up and purchase something.

Shops.Name: House of Harms
Shops.Description: Today, the law is suffering.

Name: A Notch in the Shell
Description: Skin-and-bone stalls crowd a narrow space.

Shops.Name: Uncle Ankle's Lean Place
Shops.Description: Be welcome! Here are trophies!

Name: A Bountiful Exchange
Description: How kind are the many-legged neighbours, to sell their gifts so cheaply!

Shops.Name: Spinner's Delight
Shops.Description: Come in; come in. Touch our goods. Caress them.

Shops.Name: The Fisher of Dawn
Shops.Description: This one will find treasures in a river beyond sleep. Bring a suitable antiphon.

Shops.Name: Threshold
Shops.Description: None sail East from Irem. This shop is for those who sail East from Irem.

Shops.Name: Wind-Come-Calling
Shops.Description: Tales and tales and tales.

Shops.Name: The Scuttering Company (Marine Element)
Shops.Description: The Company: ruthless, utterly professional, and the whole lot of them would fit in three big suitcases. They operate out of an undisclosed baronet's pantry. Now, they're extending their operations to the zee.

Name: Freemarket
Description: Trade unfettered by the Khanate's law.

Shops.Name: Dearly Departed
Shops.Description: Purchase what remains.

Shops.Name: Traveller's Friend
Shops.Description: Fuel, supplies, and wonders.

Shops.Name: Jonah's End
Shops.Description: A naive merchant came here in search of glory. He now makes his living selling less-rancid meat to any customer he can find.

Shops.Name: Portentum
Shops.Description: The Haruspex's disciples will take life, give death. Not yours, obviously.

Shops.Name: Requisitions
Shops.Description: A grounded zubmarine has little need for fuel. Its occupants, however, have a great need for coffee.

Shops.Name: Stonemarket
Shops.Description: Jewels; coral; rocks.

Shops.Name: The Yawning Maw
Shops.Description: A scattered assembly of traders, smugglers and shoppers.

Shops.Name: Remainder
Shops.Description: History is sacred. Ivory, less so.

Shops.Name: Dahut Exchange
Shops.Description: It could almost be Wolfstack.

Shops.Name: Hull-harvest
Shops.Description: Wrack is no longer hungers. It has other appetites to feed.

Shops.Name: Hull-harvest
Shops.Description: Wrack is replete with delights, but supplies are depleted.

Name: Rosegate
Description: The finest cigar shop above or below the waves.

Shops.Name: Proving Ground
Shops.Description: The proprietor is interested in testing the limits of flammability.

Shops.Name: Low Church
Shops.Description: Supplies for stories.

Shops.Name: Exile Bazaar
Shops.Description: The people of Hideaway have little to offer; just some oddities from the zee-bed.
